## SQLMesh MCP (via sqlmesh-mcp)

Activated for SQLMesh projects via `SQLMESH_PROJECT_DIR` in `~/.exodus/env.local`.

```
# Available via configured sqlmesh MCP server:
sqlmesh_plan           # Dry-run plan — show what would change and require backfill
sqlmesh_run            # Execute models for an environment
sqlmesh_test           # Run unit tests for one or all models
sqlmesh_table_diff     # Compare model data between two environments (e.g. prod:ci_pr_42)
sqlmesh_lineage        # Show upstream/downstream lineage for a model
```

**When to use which:**
- `sqlmesh_plan` — always run before `sqlmesh_run`; equivalent of `dbt compile`
- `sqlmesh_table_diff` — replaces the custom data diff engine for SQLMesh clients
- `sqlmesh_test` — runs unit tests in `tests/*.yaml`; supplement with `sqlmesh_plan`
